	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10213302246633>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: General question</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, May 13th 6:58 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61851><span id=Scholar>Vykore</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>179 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.05]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, some guy posted this formula on the monk boards and I would assume it would work the same for all melees. This supposedly determines your maximum damage output.<br><br>(Weapon Dmg) X (Weapon Skill + Strength) / 100 + Dmg Bonus.<br><br><br>So lets take a Centi Longsword as an example with a dmg bonus of 7 and strength of 190.<br><br><br>14 x (200 + 190) / 100 + 7 = 61.6<br><br>To show a comparrison of how much more dmg you do with an extra 20 strength...<br><br>14 x (200 + 210) / 100 + 7 = 64.4<br><br><br>As for a wurmslayer<br><br>25 x (200 +190) /100 + 7 = 104.5<br><br>And with 210 str...<br><br>25 x (200 + 210) /100 + 7 = 109.5<br><br><br>Extra damage with +20 strength may not seem like a lot but count how many times you hit the mob during a battle and then add it up and make your own opinion. <br><br>:)<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Zaviax McCleo <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432</a><br><br>Vykore Mainsnoir <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234170" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234170</a><br><br>Shadow of the Dragon<br>Tunare<br>(www.eqsod.com)</td></td></tr>
